# TDD Workflow

All new code follows Red -> Green -> Refactor. No code changes without corresponding tests.

## Test Structure

- Test files live beside code: `foo.go` -> `foo_test.go`
- Use stdlib `testing` package (no testify)
- `t.Helper()` on all test helper functions
- `t.Parallel()` on all tests and subtests

## Naming

```
TestFunctionName_scenario
```

Example: `TestCreateProject_duplicateKey`, `TestGetIssue_notFound`

## Table-Driven Tests (default pattern)

```go
func TestCreateProject(t *testing.T) {
    t.Parallel()
    tests := []struct {
        name    string
        input   model.Project
        wantErr bool
    }{
        {"valid", model.Project{Key: "FOO", Name: "Foo"}, false},
        {"empty key", model.Project{Key: "", Name: "Foo"}, true},
    }
    for _, tt := range tests {
        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {
            t.Parallel()
            // test body
        })
    }
}
```

## Test Helpers

Use `internal/testutil` for shared setup:
- `testutil.NewTestStore(t)` -- in-memory SQLite with migrations
- `testutil.SeedUser(t, st)` -- create a test user
- `testutil.SeedProject(t, st, "KEY")` -- create a test project

## Integration Tests

- Build tag: `//go:build integration`
- Run separately: `make test/integration`

## Race Detection

Always: `go test -race` (enforced in Makefile)
